# BuildKit per-Dockerfile ignore (adjacent to Dockerfile.shard).
# Allowlist style: the build context is the repo root, which carries multi-GB
# trees (.venv 1.9G, .beads 1.7G, .git 419M, service/target 515M, output,
# blog, dist, scripts/spikes 128M). Exclude everything, re-include exactly
# what the Dockerfile COPYs, then re-exclude caches inside the allowed trees.
*
!pyproject.toml
!uv.lock
!README.md
!LICENSE
!src
!tests
!scripts
!docs
!conexus
!dt
!sn
!.claude-plugin
!service/src
!service/target/nexus-service-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar
# Re-excludes (must come after the ! lines):
**/__pycache__
**/.pytest_cache
**/.DS_Store
scripts/spikes
tests/containers/out
